    public class IdentityScalarImpl
extends AbstractIdentityStemProcess
implements ProcessScalar
    Basic (identity) implementation of ProcessScalar, simply returns each argument unchanged. The default is that the dyadic calls (for stems) just call the monadic ones, so you can usually just get away with implementing one method for any type. If you want some specific error message, you have enough information for that too. This is the most permissive type of processing. This class is designed to do 95% of the work for handling aggregates and is really redundant and boring. Again, you should only need to override those things that change.
